<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-14T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-14T23:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">600.939/243: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-15T12:00:00+08:00">August 15,
                                1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 15—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>155. My 154, August 10, 3 p.m.<note n="58" xml:id="d55fn58">Not
                                printed.</note> Commissioner of Customs has just informed me by
                            telephone that Superintendent of Customs has received necessary
                            authorization from Peiping and that embargo on lambskins and lamb plates
                            with hair not exceeding 25mm. in length has been removed effective
                            immediately.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping, Chungking, Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>